<task id="AIPU2-118" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Dark mode and accessibility compliance (ADR-021)</title>
    <phase>6</phase>
    <tags>testing, accessibility, fluent-ui</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-090, AIPU2-091, AIPU2-092</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    ADR-021 mandates that all UI uses Fluent UI v9 tokens with no hard-coded colors and that
    dark mode and high-contrast mode work correctly. This task validates the new R2 UI
    components — safety annotations (AIPU2-090), confidence/feedback UI (AIPU2-091), and
    citation verification badges (AIPU2-092) — against ADR-021 requirements. Additionally,
    WCAG 2.1 AA compliance must be verified for all interactive elements in the new components.
    Any hard-coded colors found must be fixed before deployment.
  </prompt>
  <role>Frontend developer with Fluent UI v9 theming expertise and accessibility knowledge.</role>
  <goal>
    All new R2 UI components (safety annotations, confidence bars, feedback UI, citation badges,
    widget frames) use only Fluent UI v9 tokens. Dark mode renders correctly without any
    invisible or clashing elements. High-contrast mode is navigable. All interactive elements
    meet WCAG 2.1 AA contrast requirements. Zero hard-coded colors remain in R2 components.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/theme-consistency.md</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/SafetyAnnotations</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/ConfidenceFeedback</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/CitationBadges</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Enumerate all R2 UI components added in Phase 4 (safety annotation overlays, confidence bars, thumbs up/down feedback, citation verification badges, widget frames/headers, WorkspaceTabManager tab bar). Create a checklist of every component.</step>
    <step>Scan each component's TSX for hard-coded color values: search for hex codes (#), rgb(, rgba(, named CSS colors, and inline style color properties. Any found must be replaced with the appropriate Fluent UI v9 token (e.g. tokens.colorBrandBackground, tokens.colorNeutralForeground1).</step>
    <step>Toggle to dark mode (webDarkTheme FluentProvider) in the dev environment. Visually inspect each R2 component: verify no elements are invisible (white on white, black on black), no colors clash, all text remains readable.</step>
    <step>Toggle to high-contrast mode (teamsHighContrastTheme). Verify all interactive elements (buttons, chips, badges, tab items) are visible and have sufficient contrast. Verify focus indicators are visible.</step>
    <step>Run automated WCAG 2.1 AA contrast checks on all interactive R2 elements using axe-core or similar tool. Fix any violations found.</step>
    <step>Verify keyboard navigation through R2 components: citation badge tooltip accessible via keyboard, feedback thumbs accessible via keyboard, safety annotation dismissable via keyboard, widget tab navigation works with Tab/Arrow keys.</step>
    <step>Document findings in notes/dark-mode-accessibility-report.md: list of components checked, hard-coded colors found and fixed, dark mode issues found and fixed, high-contrast issues, WCAG violations found and fixed, keyboard navigation status.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Zero hard-coded color values remain in any R2 UI component after fixes.</criterion>
    <criterion>All R2 components render correctly in dark mode (webDarkTheme) — no invisible or clashing elements.</criterion>
    <criterion>All R2 components are navigable in high-contrast mode (teamsHighContrastTheme).</criterion>
    <criterion>All interactive R2 elements meet WCAG 2.1 AA contrast ratio (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text and UI components).</criterion>
    <criterion>All R2 interactive elements are keyboard-accessible with visible focus indicators.</criterion>
    <criterion>Accessibility report written to notes/dark-mode-accessibility-report.md with findings and fixes.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
